EDE</a>A premier summertime Western celebration with a rodeo, carnival, concerts, an art show, demolition derby, food, activities for the kids and other exciting happenings.&nbsp;<strong>June 26–July 7, 2019</strong><br><a href=\"https://www.colorado.com/events/greeley-stampede\">LEARN MORE</a>&nbsp;<br><a href=\"https://www.colorado.com/events/da-vinci-alive\"><br>CRESTED BUTTE ARTS FESTIVAL</a>Art demonstrations, family fun in the Art Alley Tent, a food court with local eats and drinks, and displays from 165 jury-selected artists from around the world.&nbsp;<strong>Aug. 2–4, 2019<br><br></strong><br><a href=\"https://www.colorado.com/events/da-vinci-alive\">LEARN MORE</a>&nbsp;<br>Featured Events<br><a href=\"https://www.colorado.com/articles/colorado-ghost-towns\"></a><a href=\"https://www.colorado.com/articles/colorado-ghost-towns\"><br>COLORADO GHOST TOWNS</a>Colorado ghost towns offer a peek in the foggy windows of a once-rowdy saloon, an ATV trek on roads no one bothered to pave on their way out of town and stories of intense standoffs in gulches will remind you why this was the Wild West.<br><br><a href=\"https://www.colorado.com/articles/colorado-ghost-towns\">Read More</a><br>Calendar of Events<br><a href=\"https://www.colorado.com/events/bands-bricks\"><br>Jun<br>5<br>-<br>Aug<br>7<br>BANDS ON THE BRICKS<br>Boulder<br>LEARN MORE</a><br><a href=\"https://www.colorado.com/events/116th-annual-cowboys-roundup-days-and-4th-july-celebration\"><br>Jul<br>3<br>-<br>Jul<br>6<br>116TH ANNUAL COWBOYS\' ROUNDUP DAYS AND 4TH OF JULY CELEBRATION<br>Steamboat Springs<br>LEARN MORE</a><br><a href=\"https://www.colorado.com/events/old-fashioned-4th-july-celebration\"><br>Jul<br>4<br>-<br>Jul<br>4<br>OLD FASHIONED 4TH OF JULY CELEBRATION<br>Aspen<br>LEARN MORE</a><br><a href=\"https://www.colorado.com/events/estes-park-rooftop-rodeo\"><br>Jul<br>5<br>-<br>Jul<br>10<br>ESTES PARK ROOFTOP RODEO<br>Estes park<br>LEARN MORE</a><br><a href=\"https://www.colorado.com/events/gran